ai = aye aye captain
ei = same
oi = oi in English


Consonant combinations

μπ = b, or mb as in embassy
ντ = d, nd
γκ = guh, or nguh
γγ = guh, or nguh. but γγ is only used in words of Ancient Greek origin
τζ = dz

all other 2 consonant pairs are equivalent to one sound


αυ
- av when υ followed by voiced consonant
- af when 

ευ
- ev when
- ef when

